redeem(uint256,address,address).details: Unlike conventional ERC4626 contracts, this may not always return one asset to the receiver.      Since there are no swaps involved in this function, the receiver may receive multiple      assets. The value of all the assets returned will be equal to the amount defined by      `assets` denominated in the `asset` of the cellar (eg. if `asset` is USDC and `assets`      is 1000, then the receiver will receive $1000 worth of assets in either one or many      tokens).

addPosition(uint256,address).notice: Insert a trusted position to the list of positions used by the cellar at a given index.

convertToAssets(uint256).notice: The amount of assets that the cellar would exchange for the amount of shares provided.

convertToShares(uint256).notice: The amount of shares that the cellar would exchange for the amount of assets provided.

deposit(uint256,address).notice: Deposits assets into the cellar, and returns shares to receiver.

depositLimit().notice: Maximum amount of assets per wallet. Denominated in the same decimals as the current asset.

distrustPosition(address).notice: Distrust a position to prevent it from being used by the cellar.

feeData().notice: Stores all fee data for cellar.

getPositionType(address).notice: Get the type related to a position.

getPositions().notice: Get the addresses of the positions current used by the cellar.

holdingPosition().notice: The "default" position which uses the same asset as the cellar. It is the position         deposited assets will automatically go into (perhaps while waiting to be rebalanced         to other positions) and commonly the first position withdrawn assets will be pulled         from if using orderly withdraws.

initiateShutdown().notice: Shutdown the cellar. Used in an emergency or if the cellar has been deprecated.

isPositionUsed(address).notice: Tell whether a position is currently used.

isShutdown().notice: Whether or not the contract is shutdown in case of an emergency.

isTrusted(address).notice: Tell whether a position is trusted.

lastAccrual().notice: Timestamp of when the last accrual occurred.

liquidityLimit().notice: Maximum amount of assets that can be managed by the cellar. Denominated in the same decimals         as the current asset.

maxDeposit(address).notice: Total amount of assets that can be deposited for a user.

maxMint(address).notice: Total amount of shares that can be minted for a user.

mint(uint256,address).notice: Mints shares from the cellar, and returns shares to receiver.

multicall(bytes[]).notice: Call multiple functions in the current contract and return the data from all of them if they all succeed

popPosition().notice: Remove the last position in the list of positions used by the cellar.

positions(uint256).notice: Addresses of the positions current used by the cellar.

previewDeposit(uint256).notice: Simulate the effects of depositing assets at the current block, given current on-chain conditions.

previewMint(uint256).notice: Simulate the effects of minting shares at the current block, given current on-chain conditions.

previewRedeem(uint256).notice: Simulate the effects of redeeming shares at the current block, given current on-chain conditions.

previewWithdraw(uint256).notice: Simulate the effects of withdrawing assets at the current block, given current on-chain conditions.

pushPosition(address).notice: Push a trusted position to the end of the list of positions used by the cellar.

rebalance(address,address,uint256,uint8,.notice: Move assets between positions. To move assets from/to this cellar's holdings, specify         the address of this cellar as the `fromPosition`/`toPosition`.

redeem(uint256,address,address).notice: Redeem shares to withdraw assets from the cellar.

registry().notice: Address of the platform's registry contract. Used to get the latest address of modules.

removePosition(uint256).notice: Remove the position at a given index from the list of positions used by the cellar.

replacePosition(uint256,address).notice: Replace a position at a given index with a new position.

resetHighWatermark().notice: Resets High Watermark to equal current total assets.This function can be abused by Strategists, so it should only be callable by governance.

sendFees().notice: Transfer accrued fees to the Sommelier chain to distribute.

setDepositLimit(uint256).notice: Set the per-wallet deposit limit. Uses the same decimals as the current asset.

setFeesDistributor(bytes32).notice: Set the address of the fee distributor on the Sommelier chain.

setHoldingPosition(address).notice: Set the holding position used by the cellar.

setLiquidityLimit(uint256).notice: Set the maximum liquidity that cellar can manage. Uses the same decimals as the current asset.

setPerformanceFee(uint64).notice: Set the percentage of performance fees accrued from yield.

setPlatformFee(uint64).notice: Set the percentage of platform fees accrued over a year.

setStrategistPerformanceCut(uint64).notice: Sets the Strategists cut of performance fees

setStrategistPlatformCut(uint64).notice: Sets the Strategists cut of platform fees

setWithdrawType(uint8).notice: Set the withdraw type used by the cellar.

swapPositions(uint256,uint256).notice: Swap the positions at two given indexes.

totalAssets().notice: The total amount of assets in the cellar.

trustPosition(address,uint8).notice: Trust a position to be used by the cellar.

withdraw(uint256,address,address).notice: Withdraw assets from the cellar by redeeming shares.

withdrawType().notice: The withdraw type to used by the cellar.
